<div class="reading-width">
	<%= content_tag( 'p', "#{link_to( 'Work packageable things', work_packageable_thing_list_url )} - being instruments or bills - form the focus of parliamentary #{link_to( 'work packages', work_package_list_url )}.".html_safe ) %>

	<%= content_tag( 'p', "A parliamentary work package is subject to a #{link_to( 'procedure', procedure_list_url )} and may have a #{link_to( 'calculation style', calculation_style_list_url )} set out in legislation. Work packages are formed of business items actualising one or more #{link_to( 'business steps', step_type_show_url(  :step_type => 'Jwc6nqJi' ))}.".html_safe ) %>

	<%= content_tag( 'p', "Some instruments are made under powers delegated by #{link_to( 'enabling legislation', enabling_legislation_list_url )}.".html_safe ) %>

	<%= content_tag( 'p', "Instruments and bills are made available to Parliament by #{link_to( 'organisations accountable to Parliament', organisation_accountable_to_parliament_list_url )}. Those organisations accountable to Parliament which are also government departments may sponsor bills and lead on treaties.".html_safe ) %>

	<%= content_tag( 'p', "#{link_to( 'Business steps', step_type_show_url( :step_type => 'Jwc6nqJi' ) )} may be in a #{link_to( 'House', legislature_show_url( :legislature => '4Mapsyb9' ))}, both Houses or neither House. A House is in a #{link_to( 'legislature', legislature_list_url )}. A business step may also be in a legislature, or not. They may form part of a #{link_to( 'step collection', step_collection_list_url )}, which may be related to a House or a procedure.".html_safe ) %>

	<%= content_tag( 'p', "Business steps are #{link_to( 'one type of step', step_type_list_url )}, the other types being logical and arithmetic operators and summation steps.".html_safe ) %>
	
	
	<div class="librarian-mode">
		<%= content_tag( 'h2', 'Librarian mode' ) %>
		<%= content_tag( 'p', "Some views of this website are suppressed in browsers with #{link_to( 'CSS', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CSS' )} turned on. You can enable these views by installing the client-side CSS shown below. This has been tested using #{link_to( 'Stylus', 'https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/stylus/clngdbkpkpeebahjckkjfobafhncgmne' )} in the Chrome browser. It should work in other browsers enabling client-side CSS, though no guarantees are given.".html_safe ) %>
		<pre class="overflow-auto">
			<code>
/* A user stylesheet to overide author CSS, making components marked as librarian-only visible */
body header .uk-parliament-procedure-browser-librarian-only {
	display: inline-block !important;
}
body main .uk-parliament-procedure-browser-librarian-only {
	display: inline-block !important;
}


/* Places a yellow stripe down the left of the page to indicate librarian mode */
body.uk-parliament-procedure-browser {
	background: yellow;
	padding-left: 1em;
}
			</code>
		</pre>
	</div>
</div>